rComments: He gives vague instructions and grades harshly. He's difficult to understand, doesn't give much feedback and refused to post grades online. Should have been more wary when he said multiple times in class how he wanted any feedback interactions with students to be brief. The material wasn't even that difficult, it was the prof that made it hard.

Very intimidating, tried to be interactive in class however the way he did it was a waste of time. Tough marker, marked the lab report by himself but didn't really seem to follow the lab report instructions; no rubric or making scheme was given. Not very clear when lecturing.

There is so much emphasis on the textbook. He picks random details out of hundreds of pages and ask you about it on the midterm. He will make the final extremely difficult to bring down the average because the presentation assignment is super easy. The content is all business with some science thrown in.

You may think you are doing well throughout the entire course, and then you get to the final exam and realize how screwed you are (the finals for his courses are worth 50% of your overall grade). You walk into the exam with a 4.0 GPA and then walk out of it questioning whether or not you will pass thee course.
